Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Drain and rinse @kidney beans{13.4%ounce}.

Place @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, beans, @mild red enchilada sauce{10%ounce}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and 1/3 cup water in an #8-by-8-inch baking dish{}. Season with @salt{1/4%tsp} and @pepper{}. Stir to combine, then cover tightly with #foil{}.

Bake on top rack until rice is tender, ~{35-40%minutes}.

Meanwhile, thinly slice @jalapeño{1} into rounds, removing ribs and seeds for less heat. Zest and halve @lime{1}; cut one half into wedges. Mince @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine jalapeño, juice from half the lime, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, and a small pinch of salt; toss to coat. Microwave for ~{30%seconds}; set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

In a separate small bowl, combine @sour cream{2%tablespoon} and lime zest. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Carefully remove foil from baking dish. Fluff rice and beans with a fork.

Crumble @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%ounce} and sprinkle @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup} over rice and beans. Drizzle with zesty crema. Sprinkle with cilantro and as much pickled jalapeño (draining first) as you like. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.